            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C.) In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName ref="#people/127"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Heinricus</persName> divina favente clementia
                        quartus Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus.
                        Quemadmodum ab inimicorum infestatione nullatenus est cessandum, sic
                        fidelium et amicorum voluntati est condescendendum eorumque dignę petitioni
                        diligenter satisfaciendum. Quapropter omnibus Christi nostrique fidelibus
                        tam futuris quam presentibus notum fieri volumus, qualiter rogatu et
                        petitione <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/99"
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Servitium #Shores #Immunity #Merchants #Fluvial_transport #Walls #Common_land"
                            >fidelium nostrorum <placeName ref="#places/58"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Residential #Palatium #Walls #Cities"
                                >Cremonensium</placeName></orgName> pro <rs key="#Servitium"
                            >fidelissimo servicio</rs> eorum, quecumque quondam <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">nostri privilegii</rs> auctoritate eis
                        concessimus, eadem nunc pro bonę fidei eorum perseverentia renovamus
                        renovantesque in posterum confirmamus, videlicet ea, quę suę locutionis <rs
                            key="#Common_land">proprietate communia</rs> vocant, tam quę in presenti
                        habent quam ea, quę in futuro sunt habituri, a bucca <placeName
                            ref="#places/4303" key="#Rivers">Adde</placeName> usque ad <placeName
                            ref="#places/4302">Wiperula</placeName> ex <rs key="#Shores"
                            >utraque</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4196">Padi</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Rivers">fluminis</rs> parte, et ut a <rs key="#Sea">mari</rs>
                        usque <placeName ref="#places/65">Papiam</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Immunity">secure ac libere nemine eis quicquam molestię inferente
                            eundi et redeundi</rs> et <rs key="#Merchants">mercardi</rs> secundum
                        usum et antiquam consuetudinem eorum <rs key="#Fluvial_transport">cum
                            navibus</rs> suis facultatem habeant, et per totum regnum nostrum Italię
                        secure vadant; concessimus etiam eis, ut extra <rs key="#Walls">muros</rs>
                        <rs key="#Cities">civitatis</rs> eorum deinceps <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Residential #Palatium">palatium et
                            hospicium</rs> nostrum habeamus; et bonos usus eorum et omnia, quę ex
                        fęlicis memorię predecessorum nostrorum regum sive imperatorum concessum
                        obtinuerunt, confirmamus. Si quis vero episcopus, dux, marchio, comes,
                        vicecomes, gastaldio, advocatus, scultatius contra huius nostri precepti
                        paginam ire temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">auri mille <rs
                                key="#Exotic_coins">mancosos</rs> componat</rs>, medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camerę nostrę</rs>, medietatem ei, qui dampnum vel
                        iniuriam passus est. Et ut hoc verius credatur et omni ęvo inviolabiter
                        conservetur, hanc cartam inde conscriptam et manu propria corroboratam
                        impressione nostri sigilli insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Heinrici quarti
                        Romanorum imperatoris invictissimi. (M.9.) (SI.3.) <persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Bruno">Bruno</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> recognovit. Data III. nonas iunii,
                        anno dominicę incarnationis millesimo CXVmo, indictione VIII, regnante
                        Heinrico quinto rege Romanorum [ann]o VIIII, imperante IIII; actum est
                            <placeName ref="#places/1609">Warmacię</placeName>; in Christo fęliciter
                        amen. </ab>
